-- United Water to Manage New Jersey Municipal System, Record Says
-- B y   J u s t i n   D o o m
-- 2013-07-22T20:47:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-22/united-water-to-manage-new-jersey-municipal-system-record-says.html
The United Water unit of  Suez
Environnement Co. (SEV) , Europe’s second-biggest water company, agreed
to manage Allendale, New Jersey’s water system, The Record said.  The state’s Board of Public Utilities voted unanimously to
approve the agreement, which takes effect Aug. 1, according to
the New Jersey-based newspaper. United takes over billing
operations beginning Aug. 11.  United bid $590,000 to manage the system over five years,
the lowest of three offers, the Record said. The company has no
input on water rates, which the borough will continue to set,
 Veolia Environnement SA (VIE)  is Europe’s biggest water company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
